# Python Style Guide

Extends [python-basics-primer.mdc](.cursor/rules/python-basics-primer.mdc). Follow when writing or reviewing Python.

## Formatting

- 4 spaces for indentation
- Max line length 88–100 (Black default)
- Use Ruff for lint and format when available

## Imports

- Order: stdlib → third-party → local
- Use `from typing import` for type hints

## Naming

- `snake_case` for functions and variables
- `PascalCase` for classes
- `UPPER_SNAKE` for module-level constants

## Docstrings

- Google or NumPy style for public APIs
- One-liner for simple functions
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT (see minimal-comments rule)

## Error handling

- `except SpecificError:` — never bare `except`
- Use `logging` not `print` in library code

## Type hints

- Encourage for function signatures
- `Optional[T]`, `list[dict[str, Any]]` for complex types

## Testing

- pytest; co-locate or `tests/` directory
- `test_` prefix for test functions

## Anti-patterns

| Anti-pattern | Correct |
|--------------|---------|
| Manual JSON string building | `json.dumps()` |
| Env without validation | Validated config with clear errors |
